In a rapidly changing IT environment, clients from all industries look to us for trusted solutions for their increasingly complex risks and vulnerabilities. EY advises clients to understand, architect, select and implement leading-edge solutions required to efficiently run their businesses, with a focus on Digital, Data and Cloud.
The opportunity
More than ever, business is about interpreting and reacting to complex data. As Cloud Data Engineer, specialized in Azure, you’ll have the chance to build a career as unique as you are, with the global scale, support, inclusive culture and technology to become the best version of you. Join us and build an exceptional experience for yourself, and a better working world for all.
Your key responsibilities
Implement relational and non-relational data repositories;
Manage and develop data processing solutions;
Monitor and optimize data solutions;
Design Azure Data Storage solutions;
Knowledge of data security and compliance in an Azure context
Define the strategy and roadmap to implement or optimize Azure Cloud;
Preparation of technical documentation about Azure services, procedures and related operations;
Management and monitoring of Azure usage in the company (Good practices, cost monitoring, governance);
Automate and integrate solutions through collaboration;
Compare various options based on feasibility and impact, proposing measurable plans and roadmaps that balance tactical and strategic needs;
Provide regular updates about cloud platforms direction and release plans;
Understand EY and its service lines and actively assess/present ways to serve clients;
Demonstrate ability to assimilate new knowledge;
Contribute to the team’s good productivity and motivation with good communication and cooperation to guarantee the best results.
Skills and attributes for success
Autonomy in performing tasks and finding solutions;
Motivation to ensure continuous personal growth;
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with an ability to think critically and identify creative solutions outside of the box and thrive on new challenges;
Excellent communication skills, oral and written;
Willing to join a young and dynamic team in a challenging environment;
A strong work ethic, technical rigor and attention to detail;
Professional responsibility, confidentiality and integrity;
Efficient, innovative and team-oriented work environment;
Dedicated, innovative, resourceful and able to work under pressure.
To qualify for the role, you must have
Academic education in Computer Engineering or simila fields of study;
Master’s degree in data areas (e.g. Business Intelligence, Data Science, etc) are valued;
At least 2 years of professional in the design, development and delivery of solutions in Microsoft Azure;
At least 2 years of professional experience of analysis and management of technical and functional business requirements, focusing on Microsoft Azure architecture;
Relevant experience in Azure Assessment, Migration and Project Implementation Plans;
Background in consulting environment is preferrable;
Relevant technological certifications;
Full English Proficiency.
Ideally, you’ll also have
Azure Certifications;
Knowledge in drawing and modeling techniques;
Azure DevOps build and release pipelines.
What we look for
Highly motivated individuals with excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to prioritize shifting workloads in a rapidly changing industry. An effective communicator, you’ll be a confident team player equipped with strong people management skills and a genuine passion to make things happen in a dynamic organization. If you’re ready to take on a wide range of responsibilities and are committed to seeking out new ways to make a difference, this role is for you.
What working at EY offers
We offer a competitive remuneration package and includes support for flexible working and career development. Plus, we offer: support, coaching and feedback from some of the most engaging colleagues around the world and opportunities to develop new skills and progress your career.
About EY
As a global leader in assurance, tax, transaction and advisory services, we’re using the finance products, expertise and systems we’ve developed to build a better working world. That starts with a culture that believes in giving you the training, opportunities and creative freedom to make things better. Whenever you join, however long you stay, the exceptional EY experience lasts a lifetime. And with a commitment to hiring and developing the most passionate people, feedback is an essential part of what we do and this will be forthcoming in order for you to maximize your potential and be part of a dynamic team.
If you can confidently demonstrate that you meet the criteria above, please contact us as soon as possible.
Join us in building a better working world.
Apply now!

